# tlh/tarot.ftl — Klingon (tlhIngan Hol) translation
#
# Status: DRAFT — LOW CONFIDENCE. Tarot's Italian/European mystical tradition
# has no Klingon cultural analog. Major Arcana names are heavy coinages
# following Klingon morphology with explanatory back-translations. A few
# entries land cleanly on attested vocabulary (HoS "strength", ruv "justice",
# Hov "star", maS "moon", jul "sun", veqlargh "Fek'lhr/devil", Hegh "death",
# qo' "world"); most are speculative compounds.
#
# Notation: same as tlh/french.ftl (# attested / # coinage).
#
# Schema note: follows the en-US `name-rank-tarot-special-` prefix.
#
# Needs: KLI-savvy reviewer with Tarot familiarity. This is the most
# speculative file in tlh/; promotion may require significant revision or
# alternative coinages, especially for Magician, High Priestess, Hierophant,
# Hanged Man, and Judgement.

